    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a bash script you can run:\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# Remove config files\nrm -rf /etc/llama-instance/*\nrm -rf /etc/llama-service *\nrm -rf /etc/llama-service-clickhouse \n\n# Remove log files\nrm -rf /var/log/llama-service/*\nrm -rf /var/log/llama-instance/*\nrm -rf /var/log/llama-sorting \n\n# Cleanup any remaining directories\nrm -rf /var/log/llama-service/clickhouse\nrm -rf /var/log/llama-instance/clickhouse\n```\nPlease note: This script may delete important files and data. Make sure to back up any critical files or databases before running this script. If you're still unsure, consider manually reviewing the directories to ensure you're deleting everything you need to, rather than deleting something important. \n\nRun the script as root (`sudo` or last login command), replacing `sudo` with your own root password if you are the root user.",
      "source": "target",
